message:
fix(fr-command): GEODIST trailing-args emit syntax error [bd-frankenredis-b6yj]

Upstream commands.def declares GEODIST with arity = -4. The
trailing-args branch in geo.c::geodistCommand explicitly emits
'ERR syntax error' for argc > 5:

  } else if (c->argc > 5) {
      addReplyErrorObject(c, shared.syntaxerr);
      return;
  }

fr-command's strict argv.len() != 4 && argv.len() != 5 check
mapped to 'wrong number of arguments for geodist command' instead.

Split: argc < 4 → WrongArity, argc > 5 → SyntaxError. The
existing argc==4|5 dispatch path is unchanged.

